REPL - read eval print loop

All types are object infereing from scala.Any

val are immutable[constant] whereas var are muttable variables

def function_name (parameter_name : parameter_type [,]) : return_type = functione_definition

def bToI (bvar : Boolean) = if(bvar = true) 1 else "0"
 -return type is inffered as Any , caus 1 & "0" are returnable
def bToI (bvar : Boolean) : Int = if(bvar = true) 1 else "0"
 -error caus "0" is not type INT
def bToI (bvar : Boolean) : Int = if(bvar = true) 1 else 0
 -return type is Int


docs.scala-lang.org/style


sbt --> console [gives a REPL] --> :q [exit REPL] --> exit

create scala project
  touch build.sbt && start build.sbt
    name := "File Searcher

    version := "0.1"

    scalaVersion := "2.10.4"
  blank line b/w each settings act as setting terminator
  these settings are used to create JAR files

 mkdir project && touch project\build.properties && start project\build.properties
   sbt.version = 0.13.1

 touch project\plugin.sbt && start project\plugin.sbt
   addSbtPlugin("com.typesafe.sbteclipse" % "sbteclipse-plugin" % "2.4.0")
 -maven dependency resolutionstyle

